hondo717: |cp||at|OK, let us discuss the auction first.  moe has 2 choices of bids, either 2@D or 2N. I prefer 2N, because it is more descriptive and more preemptive. However, the downside of 2N is it is also more descriptive to the opponents. As for what kia should bid. He is right on the border of a limit raise. However, in general, queens and jacks with no supporting aces and kings should be downgraded. So I think he is just short of a limit raise, because all his points are in Qs and Js.  On the plus side, he has 9s and 10s to go with his Qs and Js, so it is close. |
