hondo717: |cp||at|Opening leads are very difficult, so if you follow my guidelines, they tend to work out best, although sometimes they still cost. Some of my guidelines are as follows:|cp|8|at|
1) In a suit contract, never lead an ace (unless you have Ax and partner bid the suit), or away from an ace
2) lead partner's suit
3) lead an unbid suit
4) don't lead a singleton trump.|cp||
