hondo717: |cp||at|I play negative doubles through 3 spades.  By negative doubles, I mean you are guaranteeing 4+ cards in the unbid major. your minor suit holdings not as important. As to the number of hcp I will give you some guidelines, but a lot has to do with where your hcp are. Remember, you should tend to discount high cards in the opponents suit (even aces) and upgrade high cards in partner's suits. The reason you discount high cards in the opponents suit is that it is less likely that partner has honors in that suit, and combinations of honors work much better than isolated honors.|
