hondo717: |cp||at|OK, there are some issues regarding 2@C openers that I would like to mention.  aggie certainly has a 2@C opener. However, it is always problematical to open 2@C with a long diamond suit, because the auction usually goes 2@C-2@D-3@D and  the wrong hand often ends up as Declarer, and the bidding gets awfully high awfully fast. When you have a marginal 2@C opener with long diamonds or even clubs, usually it is better to open 1 than 2. Now, let me explain ways to respond to 2@C.|
