hondo717: |cp||at|The idea is that controls are important for slam bids, and 2@C is forcing to game. So, if you play 2@H is no controls, then a 2N bid by responder is how you show a heart suit. It is a little confusing, but hopefully you can figure out why the 2N bid is needed if you play 2@H is bust. Finally, over 2@C some people respond with the number of controls they have. A king is considered "1 control" an ace is considered "2 controls."|
