NT||cp|8|at|^B@2
hondo717: |cp||at|So, if you play control responses, 2@D shows 0 or 1 control (no more than 1 king), 2@H shows 2 controls (an ace or 2 kings), 2@S shows an ace and a king, and 2N shows 3 kings, 3C shows 4+ controls (but never comes up.)  I do not recommend that system, as it often wrong side gets the contract and may get you too high.  I recommend you play 2@D waiting, new suits show good suits, and, optionally 2@H shows no controls.|
